{"id": "EUVD-2014-4102", "enisaUuid": "0aba1fe7-9873-33bd-8c81-46fbb0e28c87", "description": "mm/shmem.c in the Linux kernel through 3.15.1 does not properly implement the interaction between range notification and hole punching, which allows local users to cause a denial of service (i_mutex hold) by using the mmap system call to access a hole, as demonstrated by interfering with intended shmem activity by blocking completion of (1) an MADV_REMOVE madvise call or (2) an FALLOC_FL_PUNCH_HOLE fallocate call.", "datePublished": "2014-06-23T10:00:00", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-06T11:04:28", "baseScore": 4.7, "baseScoreVersion": "2.0", "baseScoreVector": "AV:L/AC:M/Au:N/C:N/I:N/A:C", "references": ["https://www.suse.com/security/cve/CVE-2014-4171.html", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2015:0102", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2014:1318", "https://ubuntu.com/security/CVE-2014-4171", "https://advisories.mageia.org/CVE-2014-4171.html", "https://linux.oracle.com/cve/CVE-2014-4171.html", "http://marc.info/?l=linux-mm-commits&m=140303745420549&w=2", "http://rhn.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2014-1318.html", "https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1111180", "http://www.securityfocus.com/bid/68157", "http://lists.opensuse.org/opensuse-security-announce/2014-10/msg00006.html", "http://www.ubuntu.com/usn/USN-2335-1", "http://www.ubuntu.com/usn/USN-2334-1", "http://ozlabs.org/~akpm/mmots/broken-out/shmem-fix-faulting-into-a-hole-while-its-punched.patch", "http://lists.opensuse.org/opensuse-security-announce/2014-10/msg00007.html", "http://secunia.com/advisories/60564", "http://secunia.com/advisories/59777", "http://www.securitytracker.com/id/1030450", "http://www.openwall.com/lists/oss-security/2014/06/18/11", "http://rhn.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2015-0102.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2014-4171"], "assigner": "mitre", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "ac424885-dd99-3321-9a4d-6fc04d95f19d", "product": {"name": "n/a"}, "product_version": "n/a"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id":